    ("Groundwater flow models (like MODFLOW) simulate:", ["only surface water flow in rivers and streams today", "the movement of water through aquifer systems underground", "only ocean circulation patterns in deep water basins", "only rainfall patterns without any subsurface component"], 1, "Essential for water resource management and contamination tracking."),
    ("Landscape evolution models combine:", ["only erosion without any deposition or tectonic processes", "tectonic uplift, weathering, erosion, and sediment transport over millions of years", "only human land use changes over the past century", "only glacial processes and not any fluvial or tectonic activity"], 1, "These models reproduce mountain building and valley formation."),
