    ("Geochemical modeling tracks:", ["only physical rock properties like hardness and color", "chemical reactions between minerals, fluids, and gases in Earth systems", "only biological processes in soil and sediment environments", "only atmospheric chemistry without any geological connections"], 1, "Predicts mineral stability, fluid composition, and reaction rates."),
    ("Monte Carlo methods in geological modeling use:", ["only single deterministic values for every parameter", "random sampling of input parameters to produce probability distributions of outcomes", "no mathematical techniques whatsoever in their approach", "only historically measured values without any statistical analysis"], 1, "Accounts for uncertainty in geological parameters."),
    ("Stratigraphic models simulate:", ["only the formation of a single rock layer in isolation", "sediment accumulation, erosion, and basin filling over geological time", "only metamorphic processes in deep crustal environments", "only volcanic activity without considering sedimentary processes"], 1, "Used in petroleum exploration and basin analysis."),
    ("Glacier flow models incorporate:", ["only air temperature data and nothing about ice properties", "ice rheology, basal sliding, temperature, and mass balance interactions", "only the surface area of glaciers measured from satellites", "only historical photographs of glaciers without physics equations"], 1, "Ice flow responds to temperature, stress, and bed conditions."),
    ("Model validation for geological processes is challenging because:", ["all geological processes occur on observable human timescales", "many processes operate over timescales far longer than observational records", "there is no geological evidence to compare models against", "geological models are never validated in any scientific study"], 1, "We use geological records and analogue studies for validation."),
    ("Numerical weather prediction and geological modeling share:", ["no common computational techniques or principles at all", "mathematical methods for solving differential equations on spatial grids", "identical timescales and spatial resolutions for all models", "only the same programming language and nothing else"], 1, "Both discretize space and solve evolution equations."),
    ("Landslide susceptibility models combine:", ["only rainfall data and nothing about terrain or soil", "slope angle, soil type, vegetation, rainfall, and seismic activity data", "only population density maps and building locations", "only river flow data without any slope information"], 1, "Multi-factor analysis identifies high-risk areas."),
